---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'

export const prerender = true

const repo = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_REPO_URL
const discord = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_DISCORD_URL
---

<Base
	title='Contribute'
	description='How to contribute to Pyrrhic Stars. The whole project is open source.'
>
	<main class='mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-24'>
		<header class='mb-10'>
			<p class='text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-chrome-400 font-medium'>
				Open source
			</p>
			<h1 class='mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text-primary'>
				How to contribute.
			</h1>
		</header>

		<div class='prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text-secondary'>
			<p>
				Anyone is welcome to contribute. The whole thing is open source, under the AGPL.
				I come from backend development, so the spots where I need help most are probably
				obvious to anyone who has played the build.
			</p>

			<h2>Where I need help most</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Art and animation.</strong> Graphics, good PBR materials, and especially
					rigging, meshes, and animation. This is my weakest area by far.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>The world.</strong> More nuance: NPCs, set dressing, detailing.
				</li>
				<li><strong>Sound and music.</strong> Extremely welcome.</li>
				<li><strong>Code.</strong> Debugging, advancing features, refactoring.</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Feedback.</strong> What feels good, what falls flat, what is confusing.
					Honestly the most useful thing at this stage.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Getting started</h2>
			<p>
				{
					repo ? (
						<Fragment>
							The code lives <a href={repo}>on the public repository</a>. Open an issue or a
							pull request.
						</Fragment>
					) : (
						<Fragment>The public repository link is coming soon.</Fragment>
					)
				}
			</p>

			<h2>Get in touch</h2>
			<p>
				{
					discord ? (
						<Fragment>
							Say hi <a href={discord}>on Discord</a>.
						</Fragment>
					) : (
						<Fragment>A Discord is coming soon.</Fragment>
					)
				}
			</p>
		</div>
	</main>
</Base>
